name: Aunt Kaye's Rhubarb Dump Cake
author: SCOOBYVC
summary: My Aunt Kaye would make this every summer. It smells so good when it is cooking. She also use many different combinations of fresh fruit and flavored gelatin. Be creative and try it out.
ingredients: 1 pound rhubarb, cut into 1/4 inch slices
1 (3 ounce) package strawberry flavored Jell-O® mix
directions: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C)
Spread the rhubarb evenly in the bottom of the buttered baking dish
Sprinkle the sugar over the rhubarb, followed by the gelatin mix, and finally the cake mix
Pour the water and melted margarine over the top
Bake for 45 minutes in the preheated oven, or until the rhubarb is tender
